  "text": "Prometheus implements comprehensive TLS configuration across all external interfaces through a centralized configuration management system.\n\n## Configuration Framework\n\nAt the core, prometheus/prometheus/config/config.go defines the TLS configuration structures. The primary configuration types that handle TLS are:\n\n1. **ScrapeConfig (line 747)**: Embedded HTTPClientConfig field for scrape target connections\n2. **RemoteWriteConfig (line 1419)**: Embedded HTTPClientConfig field for remote write endpoints  \n3. **RemoteReadConfig (line 1587)**: Embedded HTTPClientConfig field for remote read endpoints\n4. **AlertmanagerConfig (line 1300)**: Embedded HTTPClientConfig field for alertmanager communication\n5. **TracingConfig (line 1159)**: Explicit TLSConfig field (line 1165) for OTLP tracing exporters\n\nThese configurations inherit from github.com/prometheus/common/config which provides HTTPClientConfig and TLSConfig with full TLS support including certificate validation, client certificates, and insecure skip verification options.\n\n## Scrape Targets\n\nScrape target TLS configuration flows through:\n- prometheus/prometheus/scrape/scrape.go: newScrapePool() creates HTTP clients via newScrapeClient() \n- newScrapeClient() calls config_util.NewClientFromConfig() with cfg.HTTPClientConfig\n- This applies TLS settings from ScrapeConfig.HTTPClientConfig to all scrape connections\n\n## Remote Storage\n\nRemote read and write TLS configuration:\n- prometheus/prometheus/storage/remote/client.go: ClientConfig contains HTTPClientConfig (line 131)\n- NewReadClient() (line 151) and NewWriteClient() (line 183) both call config_util.NewClientFromConfig() with conf.HTTPClientConfig\n- TLS is enforced through HTTPClientConfig validation and application\n\n## Service Discovery Plugins\n\nAll service discovery plugins configure TLS uniformly through HTTPClientConfig:\n- AWS SD plugins (ec2.go, ecs.go, elasticache.go, lightsail.go, msk.go, aws.go): HTTPClientConfig usage\n- Cloud providers (azure.go, digitalocean.go, gce.go, hetzner/*, ionos/*, openstack.go, scaleway/*, stackit/*, vultr.go)\n- Kubernetes (kubernetes.go): Uses NewRoundTripperFromConfig() with HTTPClientConfig\n- HTTP SD (http/http.go): Direct NewClientFromConfig() usage\n- Orchestration (consul.go, eureka.go, marathon.go, nomad.go)\n- Container platforms (docker.go, dockerswarm.go, triton.go)\n- Other services (puppetdb.go, uyuni.go)\n- XDS integration (xds/client.go, xds/xds.go, xds/kuma.go)\n\n## Tracing Exporters\n\nOTLP tracing TLS configuration:\n- prometheus/prometheus/tracing/tracing.go: Manager.ApplyConfig() (line 71) checks and applies TracingConfig with TLSConfig (line 75-76)\n- buildTracerProvider() creates OTLP client with TLS credentials\n- config_util.NewTLSConfig() is called for both gRPC (line 189) and HTTP (line 222) exporters\n\n## Web Server\n\nPrometheus web server TLS:\n- cmd/prometheus/main.go: Imports toolkit_web (line 55) and validates web config (line 1145)\n- web/web.go: Invokes toolkit_web.ServeMultiple() with FlagConfig containing web TLS configuration (line 760)\n- Web server TLS is configured via external web configuration file referenced by --web.config.file flag\n\n## Alerting\n\nAlertmanager communication TLS:\n- notifier/alertmanagerset.go: Uses config_util.NewClientFromConfig() with cfg.HTTPClientConfig (line 51)\n- AlertmanagerConfig validation ensures HTTPClientConfig is properly validated before use\n\n## TLS Validation\n\nAll configurations go through validation:\n- ScrapeConfig.UnmarshalYAML() validates HTTPClientConfig (line 858)\n- RemoteWriteConfig.UnmarshalYAML() validates HTTPClientConfig (line 1473)\n- RemoteReadConfig.UnmarshalYAML() validates HTTPClientConfig (line 1628)\n- AlertmanagerConfig.UnmarshalYAML() validates HTTPClientConfig (line 1340)\n- TracingConfig.UnmarshalYAML() validates endpoint and other fields (line 1176-1200)\n\nTLS is consistently applied through prometheus/common's config.HTTPClientConfig which handles:\n- Certificate files (CAFile, CertFile, KeyFile)\n- Server verification (InsecureSkipVerify)\n- Proxy settings\n- Custom headers and authentication\n\nThe unified approach ensures TLS configuration enforcement across all external interfaces: scrape targets, remote storage endpoints, service discovery APIs, tracing exporters, alertmanagers, and the web server."
}

